      "role": "user",
      "content": "that metallic object... if that's what LADS was actually tracking, it would suggest it wasn't just some random rock. it would mean they found something technological or artificial. if the government was truly able to scrub this from the official record, they must have had a massive system in place to control the narrative. how would someone even begin to cross-reference these redacted telemetry gaps with the unclassified geological reports from that era? is there a way to find the \"shadow\" data that doesn't match the official mission timeline?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
